DESCRIPTION:Featuring:&#160\;  Prof. Kyung-A Kim (김경아 교수님) : Piri\, Taepyeo
 ngso  Eun-sun (Sunny) Jung (정은선) : Gayageum  Hye-Jin Lee (이혜진) : Pansori&#1
 60\;  Dae-Ho Kim (김대호) : Saenghwang\, Piri&#160\;  Jeong-Pin Yoon (윤정빈) : H
 aegeum  Seo-Jeong Kim (김서��) : Traditional Percussion&#160\;  &#160\;Concer
 t Program:Piri Solo –Sangnyeongsan    A foundational court-music piece from
  the yeongsan hoesang suite\, Sangnyeongsan highlights the piri's deep\, re
 sonant tone and its expressive breath-driven phrasing. This version feature
 s a refined solo interpretation centered on its serene melodic lines.  Gaya
 geum Solo –ChunseolChunseol ("Spring Snow") is a modern classic by Hwang By
 eong-gi\, composed for the expanded 25-string gayageum. Its delicate lyrici
 sm and contemporary techniques are supported by janggu accompaniment\, show
 casing both virtuosity and subtle emotional depth.  Saenghwang Solo – Minyo
 Fantasy    The saenghwang\, a rare Korean mouth-organ capable of producing 
 sustained chords\, creates an ethereal and meditative sound world. Minyo(Fo
 lk Song) Fantasy blends traditional melodic fragments with harmonic texture
 s unique to the instrument\, accompanied by janggu.  Haegeum –Gyemyeong-gok
     A lyrical and expressive work for haegeum\, Gyemyeong-gok captures the 
 instrument's distinctive timbre—its subtle vibrato\, bending tones\, and si
 nging quality. The piece unfolds as a poetic meditation\, supported by jang
 gu rhythms.  PansoriHeungbo-ga: "Bak-taneun Daemok" (Splitting the Gourd)  
   This dramatic excerpt follows Heungbo as he opens the magical gourd. Thro
 ugh expressive storytelling\, rhythmic dialogue\, and vocal nuance\, the sc
 ene reveals both humor and tension characteristic of Heungbo-ga.  Ensemble 
 –Beautiful Country    A celebrated Korean crossover work composed by Han Ta
 e-su\, Beautiful Country blends traditional rhythmic patterns—such as gutge
 ori jangdan—with a contemporary melodic style.  K-popDemon HuntersOST    Th
 emes from the Sony animated project K-pop Demon Hunters are reinterpreted t
 hrough Korean traditional instruments\, transforming the soundtrack into a 
 unique gugak-based crossover experience.
LAST-MODIFIED:20260122T185832Z
LOCATION:Global and International Studies Building - Room Number: Shreve Au
 ditorium
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Enlightened Connections: Bridge to Korean Music
