DESCRIPTION:The American Pirates offer a genre-defying take on the American
  Songbook\, blending reimagined pre-World War II jazz standards with origin
 al music.\n\nFeaturing award-winning New York City-based pianist Albert New
 berry\, whose jazz-inflected style spans classical\, gospel\, and stride.\n
 \nLocation: MAC 066 (orchestral rehearsal rooms behind the IU Musical Arts 
 Center)\n\nAdmission: Free\n\nHear samples from their album at www.ampirate
 s.com\nTheir first studio album "What a Friend" recorded at Echo Park Studi
 os will be available at the show.
