CREATED:20260113T144941Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Tortilla Jackson is a high-energy <b>Latin jazz and funk ens
 emble</b> based in Bloomington\, Indiana.<sup></sup> They are well-known in
  the local music scene for their playful improvisation and a genre-blending
  sound that draws heavy inspiration from legendary artists like <b>Willie B
 obo\, Mongo Santamaría\, and James Brown</b>.<sup></sup></p><p></p><p>The g
 roup is frequently associated with the Indiana University Jacobs School of 
 Music. While they have performed under the direction of Professor Greg Ward
 \, they are also recognized for their student-led initiative\, showcasing t
 he talent of the next generation of jazz artists in the Midwest.</p><br>Lat
 in jazz ensemble — all ages. Doors open at 5:30 PM. 🎟️ $11.33 with food or
  drink purchase<br>More: <a href="https://dice.fm/event/7dpdb7-tortilla-jac
 kson" target="_blank">https://dice.fm/event/7dpdb7-tortilla-jackson</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260113T150606Z
LOCATION:The Orbit Room\, 107 N College Ave # 1\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, 
 USA
SEQUENCE:0
