DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20230518
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20230522
DTSTAMP:20260320T014627Z
UID:6tjf4uofgsm7mlqk33ieli55nn@google.com
CREATED:20230329T130058Z
DESCRIPTION:The state’s largest “moto &amp\; music” festival\, Tennessee Mo
 torcycles &amp\; Music Revival’s Sixth annual festivities are returning to 
 Loretta Lynn’s Ranch in Hurricane Mills\, just an hour west of Nashville on
  May 18 - 21\, 2023. This year’s headliners include Paul Cauthen\, who boos
 ts a rich\, resonant\, bass-leaning tenor dubbed Big Velvet\, “The First La
 dy of Outlaw Country” Nikki Lane\, chart-topping singer/songwriter Elvie Sh
 ane\, and heir of the original outlaw family Whey Jennings. <br><br>Tickets
  start as low as $129 for the entire event including all the live music\, m
 otorcycle action\, and good times to be had.  Subscribers save $20 and earl
 y birds save $10. Daily tickets and VIP upgrades are available.  RV\, glamp
 ing\, tent\, and van camping are available on Loretta Lynn’s Ranch.  Visit 
 MotorcyclesAndMusic.com for more details. Public early bird tickets are ava
 ilable now. Buy <em><a href="https://t.e2ma.net/click/vxz54f/fdxpxb/nfoymv"
 >here</a></em>. <br><br>Hipsters to retirees and everyone in between will e
 njoy Harley-Davidson® demo rides\, motorcycle races\, trail riding\, vendor
 s\, and the twist that makes it “Nashville”—plenty of live music on stage a
 nd by creekside and all over the ranch at the Harley-Davidson® sponsored ev
 ent. In addition to the aforementioned headliners\, TMMR is bringing in a h
 ost of other artists including Rob Lienes\, who recently toured with Dwight
  Yoakam\, War Hippies\, a rising country duo currently touring with Travis 
 Tritt\, El Dorodo\, some of who may look familiar as members Tyler Childers
 ’ band\, The Food Stamps\, but is a honky Tonk endeavor all of their own\, 
 Booray\, Chris Garner\, Jericho Rose\, Lulu\, and The Black Sheep. There wi
 ll also be a special tribute to the late Loretta Lynn featuring Tayla Lynn\
 , Ernie Lynn\, Emmy Russell\, Summer Dean\, Rob Lienes\, Coal Miner’s Band\
 , and more. <br><br>The must-attend event for motorcycle and music lovers a
 like also boosts a two-wheeled playground featuring thrilling stunt shows\,
  bike shows\, field games\, motorcycle racing\, and off-road trail riding. 
 The BC Moto Invitational\, a custom motorcycle showcase\, features select c
 raftsmen displaying some of the country’s best custom motorcycles. <br><br>
 For music lovers\, it’s paradise staying on the late Queen of Country’s ran
 ch\, enjoying headliners\, singer-songwriters\, and emerging artists playin
 g late into the night.<br><br>Winner of <em>Cycle Source Magazine</em>’s Re
 aders Choice Event 2021\, TMMR encourages attendees to camp at the ranch fo
 r the most immersive experience—three campgrounds serve campers\, RV’ers\, 
 and glampers\, and there are many hotels nearby.<br><br>Guests can also tou
 r the museums and shops in the ranch’s Western Town. The ranch is located a
 t 8000 Highway 13 South in Hurricane Mills\, TN 37078. See the TMMR website
  for more information\, <a href="http://motorcyclesandmusic.com/">motorcycl
 esandmus<wbr />ic.com</a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20230329T130058Z
LOCATION:Loretta Lynn's Ranch - Event Venue\, Campgrounds\, Tourism Destina
 tion\, 8000 Highway 13 South\, Hurricane Mills\, TN 37078\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Tennessee Motorcycles & Music Revival
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
