BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20250711T220000Z
DTEND:20250712T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260320T014627Z
UID:amelia-ray-tour-bloomington-20250711@calendarcrafter.ai
CREATED:20250701T165002Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Multilingual singer-songwriter and cultural storyteller Amel
 ia Ray brings The Soulveillance Tour – a five-month journey through the U.S
 .\, Canada and Europe to spread compassion in song – to town. The San Franc
 isco Bay Area native’s latest single\, “Pretending to Read\,” a poignant tr
 ack in the style of Bossa nova\, blends observation and introspection into 
 a melody that sneaks up on you like a mysterious stranger on a train. Come 
 join Ray’s network of soulful secret agents.</p><p>with CJ Reichard<br>In t
 he ’80s\, while a student at Indiana University\, CJ and her all-woman punk
  band climbed through the windows of a law school classroom\, stood on desk
 s\, and sang a tune she wrote called “I Think I’m Gonna Die (and I Know I’m
  Gonna Flunk).” Today\, CJ is still writing songs\, but now they might chro
 nicle a drunken dinner party\, the tear-down of grandpa’s house\, or the jo
 y and sadness of our headfirst dive through life.</p>🎟️ $10 admission<br>
 📍 Venue: <a href="https://www.orbitbtown.com" target="_blank">https://www.
 orbitbtown.com</a><br>🗺️ Map: <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/
 ?api=1&query=The+Orbit+Room+Bloomington+IN" target="_blank">https://www.goo
 gle.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp\;query=The+Orbit+Room+Bloomington+IN</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250709T153907Z
LOCATION:The Orbit Room\, 107 N College Ave # 1\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, 
 USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:The Soulveillance Tour with Amelia Ray and CJ Reichard
TRANSP:OPAQUE
ATTACH;FILENAME=Amelia-Ray-0OrbitRoom.jpg;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://drive.
 google.com/open?id=1KEE_TmrLXxGjAZj1KRF6dBufOyXWe7gD
END:VEVENT
