UID:20260123T230000Z-2135822@events.iu.edu
URL:https://events.iu.edu/live/events/2135675-arvo-part-at-90-listening-to-
 his-worlds-lecture-by
CREATED:20260122T185816Z
DESCRIPTION:To celebrate Pärt's 90th birthday\, Jeffers Engelhardt reflects
  on some of the worlds his music inhabits. Through Pärt\, we sense the comp
 lexities of Estonian identity. We hear music steeped in Christian liturgy a
 nd Orthodox Christian spirituality. And we encounter a musical voice giving
  sensuous expression to the formulaic. The significance of Pärt's work come
 s through the relationship of these worlds.  Jeffers Engelhardt is the Kare
 n and Brian Conway '80\, P'18 Presidential Teaching Professor of Music at A
 mherst College\, where he is affiliated with the department of religion\, p
 rograms in film and media studies and European Studies\, and the Five Colle
 ge Certificate in Ethnomusicology. He researches the relationship of music\
 , religion\, and secularity\; the sonic world of Orthodox Christianity\; co
 ntemporary Estonian culture and society\; and decolonizing movements in the
  Baltics. He teaches courses in ethnomusicology focusing on community-based
  ethnography\, music and religion\, voice and listening\, and analytical ap
 proaches to music and sound. His latest book project\, Music and Religion\,
  will be published in 2026 by Oxford University Press. Since 2016\, he has 
 served as Editor-in-Chief of the Yale Journal of Music &amp\; Religion.  En
 joy this presentation from almost anywhere in the world via LIVE@jacobs! (m
 ailto:LIVE@jacobs!)  &#160\;This event is cosponsored by The Byrnes Institu
 te (REEI)\, the Department of Musicology\, the Department of Central Eurasi
 an Studies\, Jacobs School of Music\, The Institute for European Study\, Th
 e Inner Asian and Uralic National Resource Center\, and the Estonian Embass
 y.
LAST-MODIFIED:20260122T185832Z
LOCATION:MUSIC LIBRARY &amp\; RECITAL CENTER (BESS MESHULAM SIMON MUSIC LIB
 RARY AND RECITAL CTR) SPEECH &amp\; HEARING - Room Number: Ford-Crawford Ha
 ll
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Arvo Pärt at 90: Listening to His Worlds Lecture by Jeffers Engelha
 rdt
